    "body": "### Problem\n\nAfter prolonged runtime (~several days), Neovim exhibits abnormally high memory usage (~multi-GB). Through jemalloc + jeprof analysis, significant memory consumption was traced to the `nlua_api_nvim_*get_option` functions. Certain plugins periodically call these functions in the background, and the functions appear to fail releasing memory properly.\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5aaf480e-8559-432b-9a3a-d5297cf04d5d)\n\nThe issue can be reliably reproduced and captured using valgrind in headless mode.\n\nNotably, these deprecated functions [lack the `FUNC_API_RET_ALLOC` flag](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/5371659524089b425887af1ce14bf9a374f0f234/src/nvim/api/deprecated.c#L633), whereas their replacement [`nvim_get_option` is properly annotated](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/5371659524089b425887af1ce14bf9a374f0f234/src/nvim/api/options.c#L151). While unfamiliar with Neovim's internal API mechanics, I suspect this discrepancy might correlate with the observed issues.\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `make CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=RelWithDebInfo CMAKE_EXTRA_FLAGS=\"-DCMAKE_C_FLAGS=-DEXITFREE\"`\n\n2. Valgrind reports leaks in deprecated function: `VIMRUNTIME=./runtime/ valgrind --leak-check=full -- ./build/bin/nvim -u NORC --headless +'lua print(vim.api.nvim_get_option(\"helpfile\"))' +q`\n  ```\n  ==1487761== Memcheck, a memory error detector\n  ==1487761== Copyright (C) 2002-2022, and GNU GPL'd, by Julian Seward et al.\n  ==1487761== Using Valgrind-3.22.0 and LibVEX; rerun with -h for copyright info\n  ==1487761== Command: ./build/bin/nvim -u NORC --headless +lua\\ print(vim.api.nvim_get_option(\"helpfile\")) +q\n  ==1487761==\n  ./runtime/doc/help.txt==1487761==\n  ==1487761== HEAP SUMMARY:\n  ==1487761==     in use at exit: 2,313 bytes in 18 blocks\n  ==1487761==   total heap usage: 15,234 allocs, 15,216 frees, 21,348,696 bytes allocated\n  ==1487761==\n  ==1487761== 23 bytes in 1 blocks are definitely lost in loss record 2 of 8\n  ==1487761==    at 0x4C39185: malloc (vg_replace_malloc.c:442)\n  ==1487761==    by 0x59EDC8: try_malloc (memory.c:98)\n  ==1487761==    by 0x59EF57: UnknownInlinedFun (memory.c:132)\n  ==1487761==    by 0x59EF57: arena_alloc (memory.c:637)\n  ==1487761==    by 0x59F0D6: UnknownInlinedFun (memory.c:704)\n  ==1487761==    by 0x59F0D6: arena_memdupz (memory.c:711)\n  ==1487761==    by 0x6F5B19: copy_string (helpers.c:643)\n  ==1487761==    by 0x56B9E5: optval_copy (option.c:3097)\n  ==1487761==    by 0x56BA6B: get_option_value (option.c:3342)\n  ==1487761==    by 0x56BB63: get_option_value_for (option.c:3945)\n  ==1487761==    by 0x7151AE: get_option_from (deprecated.c:746)\n  ==1487761==    by 0x715569: nvim_get_option (deprecated.c:637)\n  ==1487761==    by 0x5F603F: nlua_api_nvim_get_option.lto_priv.538 (lua_api_c_bindings.generated.h:2675)\n  ==1487761==    by 0x786C85: lj_BC_FUNCC (in /data/build/neovim/build/bin/nvim)\n  ==1487761==\n  ==1487761== LEAK SUMMARY:\n  ==1487761==    definitely lost: 23 bytes in 1 blocks\n  ==1487761==    indirectly lost: 0 bytes in 0 blocks\n  ==1487761==      possibly lost: 0 bytes in 0 blocks\n  ==1487761==    still reachable: 2,290 bytes in 17 blocks\n  ==1487761==         suppressed: 0 bytes in 0 blocks\n  ==1487761== Reachable blocks (those to which a pointer was found) are not shown.\n  ==1487761== To see them, rerun with: --leak-check=full --show-leak-kinds=all\n  ==1487761==\n  ==1487761== For lists of detected and suppressed errors, rerun with: -s\n  ==1487761== ERROR SUMMARY: 1 errors from 1 contexts (suppressed: 0 from 0)\n  ```\n\n3. No leaks in the new `nvim_get_option_value`: `VIMRUNTIME=./runtime/ valgrind --leak-check=full -- ./build/bin/nvim -u NORC --headless +'lua print(vim.api.nvim_get_option_value(\"helpfile\", {}))' +q`\n  ```\n  ==1487857== Memcheck, a memory error detector\n  ==1487857== Copyright (C) 2002-2022, and GNU GPL'd, by Julian Seward et al.\n  ==1487857== Using Valgrind-3.22.0 and LibVEX; rerun with -h for copyright info\n  ==1487857== Command: ./build/bin/nvim -u NORC --headless +lua\\ print(vim.api.nvim_get_option_value(\"helpfile\",\\ {})) +q\n  ==1487857==\n  ./runtime/doc/help.txt==1487857==\n  ==1487857== HEAP SUMMARY:\n  ==1487857==     in use at exit: 2,290 bytes in 17 blocks\n  ==1487857==   total heap usage: 15,234 allocs, 15,217 frees, 21,348,586 bytes allocated\n  ==1487857==\n  ==1487857== LEAK SUMMARY:\n  ==1487857==    definitely lost: 0 bytes in 0 blocks\n  ==1487857==    indirectly lost: 0 bytes in 0 blocks\n  ==1487857==      possibly lost: 0 bytes in 0 blocks\n  ==1487857==    still reachable: 2,290 bytes in 17 blocks\n  ==1487857==         suppressed: 0 bytes in 0 blocks\n  ==1487857== Reachable blocks (those to which a pointer was found) are not shown.\n  ==1487857== To see them, rerun with: --leak-check=full --show-leak-kinds=all\n  ==1487857==\n  ==1487857== For lists of detected and suppressed errors, rerun with: -s\n  ==1487857== ERROR SUMMARY: 0 errors from 0 contexts (suppressed: 0 from 0)\n  ```\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nHas reasonable memory consumption and does not leak resource.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1703+g878b3b89c3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfish, version 3.3.1 + tmux 3.6\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
